						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 5) in the inner <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Mahāliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>1416-17 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land by Kōṭi-seṭṭi of Sūrāla for feeding three Brāhmaṇas in the temple of that place during the period of Bemmaṇa-Kōri Toḷaha, when Hosabukōri was enjoying the <hi rend="italic">kumāravṛitti.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1339, Durmukhi, Śrāvaṇa,</hi> the details not being sufficient for verification. It corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1416-17 A.D.,</hi> the Śaka year being current.</p>						

						</summary>
